“Fauna” Look 2 🍄
Craterellus cornucopioides also known as horn of plenty, black trumpet or trumpet of the dead. 

The Cornucopia, in Greek mythology, referred to the magnificent horn of the nymph Amalthea's goat (or of herself in goat form), that filled itself with whatever meat or drink its owner requested. It has become the symbol of plenty.

A possible origin for the name "trumpet of the dead" is that the growing mushrooms were seen as being played as trumpets by dead people under the ground.

Every year I take on a handful of personal clients. I love doing these shoots and working one on one with individuals to capture their energy. It’s a pleasant shift from working on larger sets with lots of people. A lot of my clients are fellow creatives or business owners/professionals. Some of them are comfortable being photographed and some are not but regardless of the experience level, we usually have fun and I always feel inspired after hearing their stories, inspirations, successes and failures. Here are some of my recent favs from the past year 🖤
